<item>
            <title>[SPARK-6878] Sum on empty RDD fails with exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-6878</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Sum&lt;/tt&gt; on an empty RDD throws an exception. Expected result is &lt;tt&gt;0&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A simple fix is the replace&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;class DoubleRDDFunctions {
  def sum(): Double = self.reduce(_ + _)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 

&lt;p&gt;with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;class DoubleRDDFunctions {
  def sum(): Double = self.aggregate(0.0)(_ + _, _ + _)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
