                            <comment id="14492271" author="srowen" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2015 11:02:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Interesting question &amp;#8211; what&apos;s the expected sum of nothing at all? although I can see the argument both ways, 0 is probably the better result since &lt;tt&gt;Array&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Double&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;().sum&lt;/tt&gt; is 0. So &lt;tt&gt;sc.parallelize(Array&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Double&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;()).sum&lt;/tt&gt; should as well. Want to make a PR?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14492282" author="erikvanoosten" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2015 11:15:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The answer is only defined because the RDD is an &lt;tt&gt;RDD&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Double&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sure, I&apos;ll make a PR.&lt;br/&gt;
Is the proposed solution acceptable?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14492284" author="srowen" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2015 11:20:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, and I think it could even be a little simpler by calling &lt;tt&gt;fold(0.0)(_ + _)&lt;/tt&gt; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14492302" author="erikvanoosten" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2015 11:43:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, yes. I now see that fold also first reduces per partition.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
